HEADWORD: orthopedics
<hw>orthopedics</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ortho-</ets> + Gr. <?/,
<?/, a child.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The art or practice of
correcting disorders or deformities of the spine and joints, or, by
extension, any deformities of the human body.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> orthopaedics, orthopedy.</syn>⟦br⟧
